<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="308" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,152,539]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,152,179]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">Distribution.</emphasis>
The presence of this species in the northern GOM is questionable (See First Record and Remarks below). However, it has been reported as occurring in the northcentral GOM at depths ranging from 
<quantity box="[1250,1415,188,215]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.85" metricValueMax="10.5" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="27" pageNumber="308" unit="m" value="785.0" valueMax="1050.0" valueMin="520.0">520 to 1050 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,152,539]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,469,224,251]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">First Record in GOM.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation collectionCode="USNM" pageId="27" pageNumber="308" specimenCode="USNM 196446" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
This species was originally described (
<bibRefCitation author="Bigelow, H. B. &amp; Schroeder, W. C." box="[916,1254,225,252]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308" pagination="161 - 244" refId="ref15895" refString="Bigelow, H. B. &amp; Schroeder, W. C. (1962) New and little known batoid fishes from the Western Atlantic. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 128 (4), 161 - 244, pl. 1." type="journal article" year="1962">Bigelow and Schroeder, 1962</bibRefCitation>
) based partially on a specimen (
<typeStatus box="[327,427,261,287]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCode box="[434,609,261,288]" collectionCode="USNM" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="27" pageNumber="308" type="Museum">USNM 196446</specimenCode>
) which is listed as “probably” originating from the northern
</materialsCitation>
GOM. There are, to our knowledge, no other confirmed specimens of this species collected from the GOM.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="308" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,152,539]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,333,359]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">Remarks.</emphasis>
As the origin of the 
<typeStatus box="[550,648,333,359]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">holotype</typeStatus>
is questionable and no other specimens are confirmed as having been collected in the northern GOM (
<accessionNumber box="[514,647,369,395]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/UF184623" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">UF 184623</accessionNumber>
, listed as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bigelow and Schroeder" authorityYear="1962" box="[758,916,369,395]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Rajidae" genus="Anacanthobatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rajiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="308" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis box="[758,916,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">S. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and collected off Louisiana is actually 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bigelow and Schroeder" authorityYear="1951" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Springeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="308" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="folirostris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">S. folirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), it is probable that this species does not occur in this region at all. If it does, it is extremely rare. All other specimens recorded from the western North Atlantic Ocean were collected off the east coast of Florida and in the Caribbean Sea off the Antilles, 
<collectingCountry box="[502,612,477,503]" name="Colombia" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[666,785,477,503]" name="Venezuela" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,152,539]" box="[199,987,512,539]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,448,512,539]" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">Conservation Status.</emphasis>
Data Deficient (as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bigelow and Schroeder" authorityYear="1962" box="[666,979,513,539]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Rajidae" genus="Anacanthobatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rajiformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="308" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis box="[666,979,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="308">Anacanthobatis longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
